Package: cic.newassumptions.newvarianceestimator
Title: cic.newassumptions.newvarianceestimator: Changes-in-Changes Estimator with Asymptotic Confidence Intervals
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Timothée Bacchi [aut, cre]
Authors@R: person("Timothée", "Bacchi", email = "timothee.bacchi@etu.minesparis.psl.eu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Timothée Bacchi <timothee.bacchi@etu.minesparis.psl.eu>
Description: Implements the Changes-in-Changes estimator and asymptotic
    confidence intervals for empirical quantile-based estimators.
    defined as the average of the quantile-transformed ranks. Provides
    asymptotic confidence intervals via a full-sample (no-split) variance estimator,
    sample-splitting, a kernel-based estimator, and bootstrap alternatives
    (percentile and standard-error). The density estimators use a single user-
    controlled bandwidth multiplier h through h_{n_2,u} = h u(1-u), with default
    choice 1/log(n_2). The package focuses on core estimation and inference
    routines; extensive diagnostic helpers have been removed and replaced by
    minimal input validation warnings.
    The core computations are written in C++ via Rcpp for performance.
    The package includes robust input validation, graceful error handling for
    missing compiled code, and pure R fallback implementations for maximum
    compatibility.
